.TH def_prog_mode 3
.SH NAME
\*Ldef_prog_mode\*O, \*Ldef_shell_mode\*O \- Saves terminal modes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*Lint def_prog_mode(\|)\*O

\*Lint def_shell_mode(\|)\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "def_prog_mode subroutine"
.iX "def_shell_mode subroutine"
.iX "def_prog_mode subroutine" "reset_prog_mode subroutine"
.iX "def_shell_mode subroutine" "reset_shell_mode subroutine"
The \*Ldef_prog_mode\*O routine
saves the current terminal modes as the \*Vprogram\*O
if the terminal is running under \*Lcurses\*O.
The stored terminal modes are used by the \*Lreset_prog_mode\*O
routine.
This function is used when the user makes a temporary exit from
\*Lcurses\*O.
.PP
The routine \*Ldef_shell_mode\*O
saves the current terminal modes as the \*Vshell\*O if
the terminal is not running under \*Lcurses\*O.
The stored terminal modes are used by the \*Lreset_shell_mode\*O
routine.
.PP
Both routines are called automatically by \*Linitscr\*O.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
The \*Ldef_prog_mode\*O and \*Ldef_shell_mode\*O
functions return OK on success and ERR on error.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
\*Linitscr\*O(3), \*Lreset_prog_mode\*O(3), \*Lreset_shell_mode\*O(3)
.EQ
